By Rabiu Sani Kano  – The Police Command in Kano State says it has so far screened 7,564 candidates in the ongoing recruitment screening exercise in the state.The Spokesman of the command, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, stated this in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Monday in Kano.Haruna said that the command had screened candidates from 24 out of the 44 local government areas of the state, adding that the remaining candidates would be screened before the end of the exercise.He said the command had provided enabling platforms to captured all the candidates who registered for the exercise, adding that a mop up exercise would also be conducted for those who had earlier missed the programme.He said that the exercise was being conducted in collaboration with community leaders and local councils’ representatives to ensure that only credible candidates participated in the event.The spokesman said the command had adopted proactive measures to ensure compliance to the COVID -19 safety protocols to protect the candidates and personnel as well as stem further spread of the virus.The said that the exercise was being conducted smoothly and had recorded impressive turnout of candidates. (NAN) By Muhammad Nasir Bashir   Dutse   -      The Jigawa State Police Command has begun the screening of 4,705 applicants for recruitment into the police, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Abdu Jinjiri, has said. Jinjiri told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Dutse on Wednesday… May 9, 2018 In "Metro" By Muhammad Nasir Bello Sokoto - The Police Command in Sokoto State on Wednesday says it has screened over 785 candidates from nine local government areas seeking to join the police as Constables. A statement by the Command Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), ASP Muhammad Sadiq, said those screened were… August 27, 2020 In "News" By Muhammad Nasir Bashir Dutse,   -  The Police Command in Jigawa has said 189 out of 1,728 candidates who sat for the Computer-Based Test (CB